Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper primarily focuses on improving network performance and proposes a new operation in forwarding nodes to support qualitative services. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions packet error and network congestion, which are security concerns in network communication. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed framework and Packet Wash directive can be applied in distributed systems to improve communication performance. 
4. cs.COMM (Computer Communication and Networks) - The paper discusses the current Internet architecture and proposes a new approach to packet delivery, which falls under the scope of computer communication and networks. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper briefly mentions a newly evolved data plane technology, called Big Packet Protocol (BPP), which could potentially fall under the scope of hardware architecture.
